'''Ahmed Basil Fadhil Al Fadhli''' ({{langx|ar|أَحْمَد بَاسِل فَاضِل الْفَضْلِيّ}}; born 19 August 1996) is an Iraqi professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for the [[Iraqi Premier League|Iraq Stars League]] club [[Al-Shorta SC|Al-Shorta]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

==Club career==
===Early years===
Basil started his career at [[Al-Taji SC|Al-Taji]] where his team earned promotion to the [[Iraqi Premier League]]. He moved to [[Al-Karkh SC|Al-Karkh]] and also earned promotion there, before spending a season at [[Al-Oloom wal-Technologia SC|Al-Oloom wal-Technologia]].<ref name="shorta">{{cite web|url=https://almadapaper.net/view.php?cat=111375|title=أحمد باسل : حراسة مرمى الشرطة ليست مجازفة|language=ar|publisher=Almada Paper|date=22 August 2014|access-date=7 January 2023}}</ref>

===Al-Shorta===
In July 2014, Basil signed for [[Al-Shorta SC|Al-Shorta]].<ref name="shorta"/> Basil made one appearance in the club's [[2018–19 Iraqi Premier League]] title-winning campaign,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/i/events/1280559080793427968|title=تفاصيل مباريات الشرطة في موسم 2018-2019|publisher=Al-Shorta SC|date=7 July 2020}}</ref> before making 35 appearances and keeping 22 clean sheets in their [[2021–22 Iraqi Premier League]] title-winning season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/i/events/1542310200518103045|title=تفاصيل مباريات الشرطة في موسم 2021-2022|publisher=Al-Shorta SC|date=30 June 2022}}</ref> He then captained Al-Shorta to the [[2022 Iraqi Super Cup]] title.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/more/domestic_leagues/news/al_shorta_win_iraq_super_cup_2.html|title=Al Shorta lift Iraq Super Cup|publisher=Asian Football Confederation|date=3 October 2022}}</ref> He remained the team's starting goalkeeper as Al-Shorta went on to win another three successive titles to make it a record four in a row.

Basil also played eleven matches for Al-Shorta in the [[AFC Champions League]] across the [[2020 AFC Champions League|2020]] and [[2021 AFC Champions League|2021]] editions,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/TheAFCCL/status/1441732917764366343|title=Ahmed Basil makes a flying save|publisher=AFC Champions League|date=25 September 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/i/events/1305583020544602114|title=تفاصيل مباريات الشرطة في موسم 2020-2021|publisher=Al-Shorta SC|date=14 September 2020}}</ref> as well as playing one match at the [[2019–20 Arab Club Champions Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/i/events/1280560906800369665|title=تفاصيل مباريات الشرطة في موسم 2019-2020|publisher=Al-Shorta SC|date=7 July 2020}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Basil played his first game with the Iraq U-23s in the 2018 AFC U-23 Championship qualifiers. He helped Iraq qualify for the tournament and was named in the final squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alsumaria.tv/news/225931|title=الاولمبي يعلن قائمته النهائية ويغادر الى الصين|language=ar|publisher=Al-Sumaria TV|date=4 January 2018|access-date=7 January 2023}}</ref>

===Senior===
Basil was called up to the Iraqi national team for the first time in September 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almaalomah.com/2020/09/25/496968/|title=مدرب المنتخب الوطني يستدعي الحارس احمد باسل لصفوف اسود الرافدين|language=ar|publisher=Al-Maloomah|date=25 September 2020|access-date=4 February 2023|archive-date=5 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201005181030/https://www.almaalomah.com/2020/09/25/496968/|url-status=bot: unknown}}</ref> Basil made his debut against [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]] on 30 December 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1201190|title=بالصور.. انتصار معنوي للعراق على الكويت قبل انطلاق خليجي 25|language=ar|publisher=Kooora|date=30 December 2022|access-date=7 January 2023}}</ref> Basil was called up to the Iraqi squad in the [[25th Arabian Gulf Cup]] which Iraq won on home soil, but the player did not make an appearance.

In 2024, Ahmed Basil was called up to the [[2024 Asian Cup]], he played the third group stage match in a 3-2 win over Vietnam.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Iraq 3-2 Vietnam (24 Jan, 2024) Final Score - ESPN (UK) |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/668949/vietnam-iraq |access-date=2024-10-25 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> Iraq were knocked out in the round of 16 following a defeat against Jordan.

